FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1781308974
OL,3,CThe Cuban Exodus: Hospital workers,
OL,4,Ctourists, young people fleeing the
OL,5,Ccountry
OL,7,FThis is further hobbling Cuba's
OL,8,Fcommand economy, which these days is
OL,9,Fcontending with rolling blackouts
OL,10,Fsometimes lasting days.
OL,12,FTourism used to provide a financial
OL,13,Flifeline, but that too is on its knees.
OL,15,FWe went to the home of Nobel Laureate
OL,16,FErnest Hemingway, which normally
OL,17,Fattracts 300 visitors a day.
OL,19,FYet we were the first foreigners there
OL,20,Ffor two weeks.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1781308974
OL,3,CThe Cuban Exodus: Hospital workers,
OL,4,Ctourists, young people fleeing the
OL,5,Ccountry
OL,7,FHis mansion, once the playground of
OL,8,FHollywood stars and literary giants,
OL,9,Fis now empty except for the staff who
OL,10,Fwait in the hope of a single visitor.
OL,12,FThe Trump administration is hoping
OL,13,Fthis maximum pressure will force the
OL,14,Fgovernment of President Miguel Diaz-
OL,15,FCanel to change course and enter
OL,16,Fmeaningful negotiations with the US to
OL,17,Fopen up and abandon its communist
OL,18,Fprinciples.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1781308974
OL,3,CThe Cuban Exodus: Hospital workers,
OL,4,Ctourists, young people fleeing the
OL,5,Ccountry
OL,7,FHowever, there is no sign of
OL,8,Fcompromise from a government which
OL,9,Fstill reveres Fidel Castro and his 95-
OL,10,Fyear-old brother Raul, who was
OL,11,Frecently indicted by the US Department
OL,12,Fof Justice.
OL,14,FThe government's defiance is
OL,15,Fentrenched, but so too is the growing
OL,16,Ffatigue of ordinary Cubans, many of
OL,17,Fwhom feel let down by 67 years of
OL,18,Fcommunist ideology, which has left
OL,19,Fmany of them starkly poorer than their
OL,20,FCaribbean and Central American
OL,21,Fneighbours.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
